public class OrderedBlockManager
extends BlockManager

This is like an OrderedEventManger except that the events are assumed to be instances of EventHandler themselves. Instead of having an EventHandler process each event, each event is asked to process an object. In other words the held object is the visitor to the event, not visa-versa.
